  "local_port": 48332,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the top 10 sightseeing sites in and near Chandigarh?",
  "response": "Chandigarh, the first planned city in India, is known for its beautiful architecture, gardens, and cultural heritage. Here are the top 10 sightseeing sites in and near Chandigarh:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Rock Garden**\n- **Description**: A unique sculpture garden built using industrial and home waste, created by Nek Chand.\n- **Highlights**: Rock sculptures, mosaic art, and water features.\n- **Location**: Sector 1, Chandigarh.\n\n---\n\n### **2. Sukhna Lake**\n- **Description**: A serene man-made lake perfect for boating, walking, and birdwatching.\n- **Highlights**: Sunrise view, pedal boating, and scenic promenade.\n- **Location**: Sector 1, Chandigarh.\n\n---\n\n### **3. Capitol Complex**\n- **Description**: A UNESCO World Heritage Site designed by Le Corbusier.\n- **Highlights**: Open Hand Monument, Secretariat, High Court, and Legislative Assembly.\n- **Location**: Sector 1, Chandigarh.\n\n---\n\n### **4. Rose Garden (Zakir Hussain Rose Garden)**\n- **Description**: Asia\u2019s largest rose garden with over 1,600 species of roses.\n- **Highlights**: Colorful flowerbeds and peaceful pathways.\n- **Location**: Sector 16, Chandigarh.\n\n---\n\n### **5. Elante Mall**\n- **Description**: One of the largest malls in North India, offering shopping, dining, and entertainment.\n- **Highlights**: Multi-brand stores, food court, and multiplex.\n- **Location**: Industrial Area, Phase 1, Chandigarh.\n\n---\n\n### **6. International Dolls Museum**\n- **Description**: A museum showcasing a collection of dolls from around the world.\n- **Highlights**: Cultural insights and unique doll displays.\n- **Location**: Bal Bhavan, Sector 23, Chandigarh.\n\n---\n\n### **7. Pinjore Gardens (Yadavindra Gardens)**\n- **Description**: A Mughal-style garden with terraced lawns, fountains, and a mini zoo.\n- **Highlights**: Evening light show and historical architecture.\n- **Location**: Pinjore (about 20 km from Chandigarh).\n\n---\n\n### **8. Morni Hills**\n- **Description**: A picturesque hill station near Chandigarh, known for its trekking trails and lakes.\n- **Highlights**: Tikkar Taal Lake and scenic views.\n- **Location**: Haryana (about 45 km from Chandigarh).\n\n---\n\n### **9. Mughal Gardens**\n- **Description**: Located at the President\u2019s Retreat Estate, these gardens are inspired by Mughal designs.\n- **Highlights**: Beautiful landscaping and seasonal flowers.\n- **Location**: Sector 3, Chandigarh.\n\n---\n\n### **10. Chhatbir Zoo (Mahendra Chaudhary Zoological Park)**\n- **Description**: A large zoo home to a variety of animals, including lions and tigers.\n- **Highlights**: Safari-like experience and wildlife conservation.\n- **Location**: Chhatbir (about 25 km from Chandigarh).\n\n---\n\nThese attractions offer a mix of nature, history, and modern architecture, making Chandigarh a must-visit destination.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
